cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper focuses on natural language understanding and specifically on natural language inference, which is a subfield of computational linguistics. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with machine learning models and their ability to learn semantic phenomena, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses BERT, a popular language model, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of images in some of the experiments, which could potentially place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
